text = "    Smallpox is an infectious disease caused by the variola virus. The history of smallpox is a long and devastating one. The disease is estimated to have killed hundreds of millions of people throughout history and played a significant role in shaping the course of human history.

    In 1796, the English physician Edward Jenner developed the first successful vaccine for smallpox, which involved inoculating people with a milder form of the disease called cowpox. This discovery revolutionized public health and led to the eventual eradication of smallpox.
